data.title: Sergio Osmeña: "Grand Old Man of Cebu"
data.meta_description: SergioOsmeña - Free download as Powerpoint Presentation (.ppt / .pptx), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or view presentation slides online. Sergio Osmeña was the fourth president of the Philippines, serving from 1944 to 1946. He was born in 1878 in Cebu City to a prominent Filipino family. Osmeña had a long political career prior to becoming president, serving in the Senate and House of Representatives. As president during World War II, he oversaw the country's liberation from Japanese occupation and restoration of the Commonwealth government. Osmeña established important foreign policies and institutions before finishing his term in 1946. He remained an influential figure in Philippine politics until his death in 1961.
